Cleaning Operations Manager
30 Apr 2014 09:19 PM - UAE
Job Description: Cleaning Operations Manager – AirsideAreas of Responsibility:All Cleaning AllocatorsCleaning SupervisorCleaning Team LeaderCleaners and DriversPurpose of the job:The purpose of this role is to oversee all Aircraft cleaners’ activities ensuring the highest performance standards and safe work environment are met and in line with the Policies and Procedures.Qualifications& Experience:High School Level / Diploma3 + years experience in related field.Management of Personnel Resources — Motivating, developing, and directing people as they work, identifying the best people for the jobManagement of Material Resources — Obtaining and seeing to the appropriate use of equipment, facilities, and materials needed to do certain workInterpersonal Abilities - Proven relationship-builder with unsurpassed interpersonal skills.Leadership/Management Skills - Goal-driven leader who maintains a productive climate and confidently motivates, mobilizes, and coaches employees to meet high performance standards.Planning/Organizing - Results-driven achiever with exemplary planning and organizational skills, along with a high degree of detail orientation.AccountabilitiesTo oversee all aircraft cleaners’ activities and to ensure that all training provided is in compliance with company cleaning standards, Customer Airlines and regulators procedures.To oversee and monitor staff levels, ensuring that all RPD functions have been updated within the allotted timescales.  These shall include daily staffing levels, leave, absence and sickness.To oversee that all staff are punctual and to protect the company’s On Time Performance.To oversee all cleaning functions ensuring all are completed satisfactorily, and in compliance with company and the Airport, Customer Airlines and any other regulatory body procedures.To oversee that all allocated cleaning vehicles and equipment are in serviceable condition and any defects found should be reported via defect reporting system.To conduct regularly briefings with Team leaders to ensure that all staff are kept up-to-date with any new procedures or regulations.To oversee and ensure that company uniform and grooming standards are maintained at all times.To ensure all staff are adequately trained to carry out their duties.To ensure that adequate staffing levels are maintained during training periods.To liaise and correspond with all of our Customer Airlines, Airport authorities and Police as required, ensuring that all enquiries and complaints are dealt with in a timely manner.To liaise and correspond with all of our Customer Airlines with regards to stock required for the cleaning of the aircraft and deal with cases of non delivery or in adequate stocks.To monitor and review the lost and found items found on Aircraft database produced by the Cleaning Allocator.To oversee and approve all annual leave based on the annual leave plan and recommendations provided by the Cleaning Allocator.To oversee and monitor expenditure relating to ISR’s raised for any non stock items.  To sign off any new items required.To effectively manage all departmental disciplinary matters, ensuring that company HR rules are adhered to and that fully completed records are kept and maintained.To ensure that company HR is kept informed of all disciplinary action taken within the section.To effectively liaise and communicate with all company departments to ensure business continuity. (more...)
